Sorting in C++ is a concept in which the elements of an array are rearranged in a logical order. 
This order can be from lowest to highest or highest to lowest.
Sorting an unsorted array helps to solve many problems such as searching for the minimum or maximum element, etc

types of sorting

1. Bubble sort
2. Selection sort.
3. Insertion sort
4. Quick sort (or) 
5. Merge Sort 
